@startuml 37_chatbot_memory_session
!theme plain
skinparam defaultFontName Segoe UI
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam rectangleBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam rectangleBackgroundColor #F8F8F8

title DRE 3D — Chatbot Memory & Session State Architecture\nDatabricks Apps + LangGraph + Delta + UC Volume

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
' CHATBOT LAYERS
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
package "DQ Chatbot App  (Databricks Apps)" as CHATBOT #EEF2FF {

    component "**Streamlit / Gradio UI**\n──────────────────\nChat interface\nSession cookie (user_id)\nConversation display" as UI #DBEAFE

    component "**LangGraph StateGraph**\n──────────────────\nIn-memory short-term state\nper graph execution:\n  messages[]\n  tool_calls[]\n  intermediate_steps[]\n  current_intent\n  active_rule_draft" as LANGGRAPH #DBEAFE

    component "**Memory Manager**\n──────────────────\nLoad: fetch last N turns\n  from session_memory table\nSave: persist each turn\nCompact: trigger when\n  turns > 10 OR tokens > 8K" as MEMMGR #DBEAFE
}

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
' MEMORY TIERS
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
package "Memory Tiers  (Databricks-native)" as MEMTIERS #F0FDF4 {

    component "**Tier 1 — Working Memory**\n(LangGraph in-process state)\n──────────────────\nScope: current agent run\nStorage: Python dict (RAM)\nPersistence: none\nEviction: end of graph run\nLatency: 0ms" as T1 #BBF7D0

    component "**Tier 2 — Session Memory**\n(Delta table: agent_session_log)\n──────────────────\nScope: current user session\nSchema: session_id, user_id,\n  turn_no, role, content,\n  tool_calls_json, ts\nPersistence: session lifetime\nLatency: <50ms\nSize: last 20 turns loaded" as T2 #BBF7D0

    component "**Tier 3 — Long-term Memory**\n(Delta table: user_rule_history)\n──────────────────\nScope: cross-session, per user\nSchema: user_id, rule_id,\n  table_fqn, check_type,\n  outcome, ts\nPersistence: permanent\nLatency: <100ms\nUse: personalised suggestions" as T3 #BBF7D0

    component "**Tier 4 — Context Snapshots**\n(UC Volume: ctx_snapshots/)\n──────────────────\nScope: compacted session history\nFormat: JSON (summary + key facts)\nTrigger: >10 turns OR >8K tokens\nPersistence: 30 days\nUse: resume long sessions" as T4 #BBF7D0
}

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
' CACHING (lightweight for small user base)
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
package "Rule Suggestion Cache  (Delta — lightweight)" as CACHE #FFF7ED {

    component "**check_suggestions_cache**\n(Delta table)\n──────────────────\nhash(table_fqn + schema_ver\n  + check_type) → suggestions_json\ncreated_ts, hit_count, expires_ts\n\n**Why Delta (not Redis):**\n• User base is small (<50 concurrent)\n• Delta reads <100ms at this scale\n• Zero additional infrastructure\n• UC lineage + audit for free\n• Invalidate on schema change" as SUGGCACHE #FED7AA

    component "**Session Deduplication**\n──────────────────\nWithin same session:\nif user asked same Q before\n→ return cached answer directly\nfrom Tier 2 (no LLM call)" as SESSIONDEDUP #FED7AA
}

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
' DATABRICKS STORAGE COMPONENTS
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
package "Databricks Storage" as DBX #FFF3E0 {
    database "agent_session_log\n(Delta — UC managed)" as SESSION_LOG #FFE0B2
    database "user_rule_history\n(Delta — UC managed)" as RULE_HIST #FFE0B2
    database "check_suggestions_cache\n(Delta — UC managed)" as CACHE_TABLE #FFE0B2
    component "ctx_snapshots/\n(UC Volume)" as SNAPSHOTS #FFE0B2
}

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
' FLOWS
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
UI -down-> LANGGRAPH : user message + session_id
LANGGRAPH -down-> MEMMGR : on each turn:\nload + save
MEMMGR -down-> T2 : read last 20 turns\nwrite current turn
MEMMGR -down-> T3 : read past rule history\nfor personalisation
MEMMGR -down-> T4 : write snapshot\nwhen compact triggered
MEMMGR -down-> SUGGCACHE : check cache before\ncalling LLM

T1 -right-> LANGGRAPH : live state
T2 -right-> SESSION_LOG
T3 -right-> RULE_HIST
T4 -right-> SNAPSHOTS
SUGGCACHE -right-> CACHE_TABLE

SESSIONDEDUP -up-> LANGGRAPH : short-circuit\n(no LLM call needed)
SUGGCACHE -down-> SESSIONDEDUP : within-session\nhit check

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
' MEMORY LIFECYCLE ANNOTATION
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
note top of MEMMGR
  **Memory load on session start:**
  1. Fetch user's last session_id from agent_session_log
  2. Load last 20 turns (Tier 2)
  3. Load user's last 5 approved rules (Tier 3)
  4. If turns > 10: load compacted snapshot (Tier 4)
     instead of raw turn history

  **On context compaction:**
  1. LLM summarises last 10 turns → 1 paragraph
  2. Snapshot written to UC Volume (Tier 4)
  3. Raw turns archived (kept for audit, not loaded)
  4. Session continues with compact context
end note

note right of SUGGCACHE
  **Cache invalidation triggers:**
  • Schema change detected on table_fqn
    → DELETE WHERE table_fqn = X
  • expires_ts < NOW() (default 7 days)
    → nightly cleanup job
  • User explicitly requests fresh suggestions
    → DELETE WHERE hash = X

  **Cache is optional** — DQ rules still work
  without it. It only saves LLM calls for
  repeated same-table queries.
end note

legend
  **37. Chatbot Memory & Session State Architecture**
  |= Memory Tier |= Storage |= Scope |= Latency |= Purpose |
  | Working memory | LangGraph state (RAM) | Current agent run | 0 ms | Tool call chaining |
  | Session memory | Delta: agent_session_log | User session | <50 ms | Conversation continuity |
  | Long-term memory | Delta: user_rule_history | Cross-session | <100 ms | Personalised suggestions |
  | Context snapshots | UC Volume: ctx_snapshots/ | Compacted history | <200 ms | Resume long sessions |
  | Rule cache | Delta: check_suggestions_cache | Per table+check_type | <100 ms | Skip LLM on repeat asks |
  --
  **WHAT**: Four-tier memory architecture for the DQ Chatbot — all Databricks-native, zero extra infrastructure.
  **HOW**: LangGraph manages in-process working memory; Memory Manager loads/saves session turns to Delta;
           compaction snapshots to UC Volume after 10 turns; rule suggestion cache in Delta (adequate for small user base).
  **ACHIEVED**: Persistent conversation context across turns and sessions; personalised suggestions per user;
                no lost context on browser refresh; zero idle memory cost.
  **MEASURED**: Session resume latency <200ms | cache hit rate >30% for repeat queries |
               compaction triggers at 10 turns (60% context token reduction).
endlegend

@enduml
